    "sections": [
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Element-wise maximum of array elements."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Compare two arrays and return a new array containing the element-wise\nmaxima. If one of the elements being compared is a NaN, then the\nnon-nan element is returned. If both elements are NaNs then the first\nis returned.  The latter distinction is important for complex NaNs,\nwhich are defined as at least one of the real or imaginary parts being\na NaN. The net effect is that NaNs are ignored when possible."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Extended Summary"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "The arrays holding the elements to be compared.\nIf "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "x1.shape != x2.shape"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": ", they must be broadcastable to a common\nshape (which becomes the shape of the output)."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "array_like",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "The arrays holding the elements to be compared.\nIf "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "x1.shape != x2.shape"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": ", they must be broadcastable to a common\nshape (which becomes the shape of the output)."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "x1, x2",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "A location into which the result is stored. If provided, it must have\na shape that the inputs broadcast to. If not provided or None,\na freshly-allocated array is returned. A tuple (possible only as a\nkeyword argument) must have length equal to the number of outputs."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "ndarray, None, or tuple of ndarray and None, optional",
                "inline": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "A location into which the result is stored. If provided, it must have\na shape that the inputs broadcast to. If not provided or None,\na freshly-allocated array is returned. A tuple (possible only as a\nkeyword argument) must have length equal to the number of outputs."
                  }
                ],
                "name": "out",
                "type": "field_list"
              },
              {
                "body_blocks": [
                  {
                    "inline": [
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "This condition is broadcast over the input. At locations where the\ncondition is True, the "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "out"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " array will be set to the ufunc result.\nElsewhere, the "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "out"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " array will retain its original value.\nNote that if an uninitialized "
